The '''Grumman Gulfstream I''' (company designation '''G-159''') is a twin-turboprop business aircraft. It first flew on August 14, 1958.

A U.S. Navy Grumman TC-4C Academe aircraft (BuNo 155727) from attack squadron VA-42 Green Pawns, at Naval Air Station, Oceana, Virginia (USA), on 1 August 1989. The TC-4C was a Gulfstream I fitted with the nose section of a Grumman A-6 (later A-6E TRAM) for bombardier/navigator training. This aircraft was retired to the AMARC as 4G0004 on 13 September 1994.
TC-4C aircraft used by VA-42 to train pilots and bombardier/navigators.
